//How much longer do you think I'll have to sit in this pool of my own blood, blind, no longer able to see the end of the world. It all happened so fast, everything was gone so fast. Now I am alone in the dark, with only the moving gears of this computer and the metallic touch of this coin giving me comfort.//


Update Containment Class: __Esoteric/Archon__

Update Disruption Class: __Ekhi__

Update Caution Class: __Critical__

Update Clearance level: __Level Five__

Lock Page

[Clink]

This anomaly is what caused the scorching of Earth and the mass extinction of almost all life: from the largest of trees to the smallest of bacteria. The location of the anomaly? Well... it's the coin that's in the palm of my hand. 

[Clink]

The anomaly was recovered in 2010 after it caused some major industrial damage. We did a few tests with it. All should've told us to leave it the hell alone. No, bury it under pounds and pounds of concrete or throw it in the Marianas Trench under a brick. 

[Clink]

I believe that the article stated that the incident involving the D-Class riot was the last one and further experimentation was suspended. That was a lie... a lie I only learned about a few days ago.

The Foundation, secre- arrgh, fu-u-u-ck me!

[He howls in inexplicable pain while shuddering and grasping what little breaths he has left]

Apologies... it's just that my current circumstances have left me in an uncomfortable position.

[He takes a deep breath, regaining his composure]

Multiple tests utilizing the anomaly were hidden from most in the Foundation. The only ones who knew about them were a select few with level five clearance, the Ethics Committee, and the O5 Council. 

Do you want to know the weirdest part of it all: none of them objected to this. Even after constant failures and unnecessary casualties... they continued. 

Countless containment breaches, constant malfunctions, and now the end.

[Clink]

[Silence]

[Clink]


Most of the tests involving the anomaly ended with unlucky before the eighth flip and in retrospect that was probably the lucky outcome, but they didn't see it that way.

[Clink]

They became obsessed with it, infatuated, angry but always going back to it for another. Even those who were originally against it.

But it wasn't those tests that did this... no, it was one... single... experiment.

Proj. Gambler's Fallacy.

Truly a perfect world. One where possibly every dangerous anomaly is retrofitted in being beneficial for us. One where the Foundation uses its assets to actively assist the common man...

All they needed was a little bit of luckâ€¦

[Clink]

It took five years for the Foundation to prepare. They took their time with every nook and cranny of this machine. Multiple tests created a prosthetic arm that could flip a coin perfectly in order to have it land on the right side.

Then they began. 

Download Proj. Gambler's Fallacy
