[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[=]]
**PROJ. GAMBLER'S FALLACY**
------
[[/=]]

**Date:** 10/03/2033

**Procedure/Notes:** This experiment will focus on fully utilizing SCP-7000 for the benefit of the Foundation. For maximum safety, the prosthetic arm, codenamed Gambler's Hand, attached to Agent Richard Perard will be used for this experiment. Gambler's Hand has been tested multiple times with coins of similar dimensions in perfect conditions. Simulations have shown Gambler's Hand flipping SCP-7000 multiple times with it landing on lucky in every instance.

This experiment shall attempt to reach 10 lucky flips.

Note: Attempts to find SCP-7000's reality alteration events will come after the experiment is done.

**Test Coordinator:** O5-13

**Test Subject:** SCP-7000

------
[Begin Log]

**O5-13:** Are we all ready? Good. Diagnostics check. Maintenance check. I think everything's ready. You good Richard?

**Richard Perard:** Yup, ready to go, sir.

**O5-13:** Then there's no reason to take any longer. 

[SCP-7000 is brought into the testing room]

**O5-13:** Are you all ready to change the world for the better. 

[Richard lifts the coin with the Gambler's Hand]

**O5-13:** Now... begin.

[SCP-7000 is flipped four consecutive times; all resulted in lucky]

**O5-13:** Good... again Richard.

[SCP-7000 is flipped four consecutive times once more; all resulted in lucky]

**O5-13:** Just two more boys. Then we can all see what will be waiting for us. 

 [Richard pauses before taking the next step]

**Richard Perard:** Are you sure we should keep going, sir?

[O5-13 stares at Richard without giving an answer]

**Richard Perard:** I-I'm sorry sir, but isn't this enough now.

**O5-13:** Please... Richard... don't make me hurt you. Flip... the... coin.

**Richard Perard:** Y-yes sir.

[Richard lifts SCP-7000, hesitantly; he looks toward O5-13 before flicking the Gambler's Hand's fingers]

**Richard Perard:** W-Wha-

[Richard stares at the anomaly, whispering something unintelligible to himself]

**O5-13:** What's the problem, Richard?

[Richard ignores O5-13, fixated on SCP-7000]

**O5-13:** What the hell's your problem? Go again!

**Richard Perard:** U-Un-U-U-

**O5-13:** Dammnit, spit it out!

**Richard Perard:** Unlucky...

[O5-13 stared at Richard with a face of disbelief and shock]

**O5-13:** Bullshit, show me the damn thi-

[O5-13 paused unable to express his shock]

**O5-13:** No, no, no. That is not possible. We ran the simulations multiple times. This shouldn't be... shit. Halt the experiment. We need to know what's going to happen! Get on it now!

------
[End Log]
