//There were no screams, there were no cries, and there were no prayers. A white light, utterly blinding, flowed into the world. All organic matter that was touched by it became nothing but ash. Every tree, every child. Old and new.//

//Nothing but ash.//

[Clink]

Number 45.
You should've seen it. It was snowing ash, it was falling all around us. It would've been a beautiful sight if the circumstances were different. It didn't take much for me to understand something... terrible has happened.

[Clink]

Logan wasn't as calm as I was. Almost immediately he began to hyperventilate. He looked over to the chair where someone should be and saw the ash that took their place. Fuck, he yelped... fuck was the same thing going on in my mind.

[Silence]

It seemed like the realization was sudden after that sight... how quiet it was. No conversations between colleagues about various anomalies. No angry shouts stemming from the D-Class. What the hell, my only friend yelled.

He ran without me, trying to find some semblance of life in this seemingly dead facility but there were patches of ash at every corner. 

We checked the offices for any of our co-workers.
Ash

We checked the holding cells for the D-Class.
Ash

We checked for potted plants.
Ash

Ash

Ash

[Clink]

Just ash...

Looking outside we knew whatever happened out there ended up making its way in here... and probably everywhere else. The trees and every blade of grass were gone. The sky was gray, now instead of clouds, only black blots of ash roamed the sky.

It felt like hell took its place on Earth's surface. Logan and I tried our best to remain calm... as calm as you can be when you're the only two things seemingly alive. We took stock of how much food we had left and stayed inside until we received something from the Foundation.

The idea of ash filling your lungs wasn't a pretty thought.

[Clink]

It was two weeks... two weeks of me and him trying to make sense of it all, for how could any of this make sense. Two weeks of wondering if our families back home were ash.

Then we received a message, specifically from Site 83.

