//Have you ever heard of liminal spaces? The concept of being somewhere so familiar, but what made it it was gone. The crowds. The smell of a busy morning in the city. The woods staring back at you during the night. We really do take these things for granted. Oh, Monika...//

[Clink]

Number 69.
After listening to the message, we didn't know what to do. Reverse it... how? What could be there that can revert all of this? It would be a two-day road trip for me and Logan to make.

It would be long and difficult considering the circumstances. The temperature rose to sixty-two degrees celsius. The air was most likely unbreathable on the outside. We would have to wear suits from the biological sector.

We'd have to leave the only safe house we know of for miles out with a vehicle that neither of us know how to fix. If one thing went wrong we were dead but... it felt that was the case anyway. We were getting sick of staying inside anyway.

[Clink]

We gathered up as many supplies as we possibly could and tossed them into the truck. For some reason, we checked one more time to see if there was anybody other than us left. Just a little bit more noise. That's all we were looking for... I think.

[Silence; Andrew takes a deep, long breath, adding on to the heat of the room]

The first few hours of the drive were silent. Logan decided to drive for the first day. He was tired... tired of all of it. He tried to keep a smile on his face; for me I guess. But I knew... we both knew. It was too damn obvious.

I simply sat in a realm of my own silence, looking out of the window just to witness the disturbing reality we were a part of now. One, two, and three hours passed. The sights were all the same, except for the size of the ash piles.

That was when I realized looking at my watch. It was daytime but the little light that came to us felt like it came from the Moon. I looked back up to the gray sky. 

The Sun no longer looked like a Sun... more like its shadow. An eclipse that was eternal. A hole in space emitting the slightest of light.

[Clink]

Did SCP-7000 do that too? How far was this thing's reach? Its ability to overhaul reality. Did that extend to the Sun as well?

I was able to get a pretty good shot of it.

